cs.CE, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it deals with the development of a scientific application for performing high fidelity predictive simulations of particle-laden explosively dispersed turbulent flows. It is also likely to belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the application is executed on parallel processors and the paper presents different load balancing algorithms for CMT-nek on large scale multicore platforms consisting of hundreds of thousands of cores. Additionally, it could belong to cs.MS (Mathematical Software) as the paper involves detailed simulations and is compute-intensive. It could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as the paper presents different load balancing algorithms and evaluates their performance. Finally, it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper involves the development of a scientific application and the presentation of different load balancing algorithms.
